netMask.name: netMask
netMask.description: The IP subnet mask for the network. The default is 255.255.255.0 (class C) which allows 254 nodes.

netNumber.name: netNumber
netNumber.description: The IP network number for the network.

netDlciAddrSig.name: netDlciAddrSig
netDlciAddrSig.description: This variable states the DLCI addressing significance.

netMaxSegsize.name: netMaxSegsize
netMaxSegsize.description: This variable states the maximum sgement size for the network.

netSmdsAreaMaskStart.name: netSmdsAreaMaskStart
netSmdsAreaMaskStart.description: This variable states the starting digit number for defining the start of the Area Mask for SMDS Addresses.

netSmdsAreaMaskDigits.name: netSmdsAreaMaskDigits
netSmdsAreaMaskDigits.description: This variable states the number of digits used for defining the Area Mask for SMDS Addresses.

aseEntry.name: aseEntry
aseEntry.description: An ASE entry contains an external NMS path accessible from the node.

aseAddr.name: aseAddr
aseAddr.description: IP Address for an external NMS.

aseMask.name: aseMask
aseMask.description: IP Address mask for an external NMS. The default value is 255.255.255.255.

aseDefaultGwAddr.name: aseDefaultGwAddr
aseDefaultGwAddr.description: Default Gateway IP Address for reaching the external NMS. This field is not applicable to NMSs which are reachable via SLIP or on the same Ethernet.

aseMetricType.name: aseMetricType
aseMetricType.description: Type of metric (1 or 2) for each external NMS. The default is 1. (This field is not applicable to SLIP- based hosts.)

aseAdminStatus.name: aseAdminStatus
aseAdminStatus.description: The desired state of the entry.

aseIfIndex.name: aseIfIndex
aseIfIndex.description: The interface value of the corresponding MIB-II ifEntry.

aseDlci.name: aseDlci
aseDlci.description: The management dlci through which the NMS communicates to the switch.

nodeIpAddr.name: nodeIpAddr
nodeIpAddr.description: The inband IP address of the node in the Cascade internal trunk IP network.

nodeLanIpAddr.name: nodeLanIpAddr
nodeLanIpAddr.description: The inband (Ethernet) IP address of the node for a NMS to access the node and the internal trunk IP network.

nodeNMSEntry.name: nodeNMSEntry
nodeNMSEntry.description: A NMS entry contains an IP address of a NMS which has extended privilages.

nodeNMSIndex.name: nodeNMSIndex
nodeNMSIndex.description: The IP address entry of a primary Network Management Station.

nodeNMSIpAddr.name: nodeNMSIpAddr
nodeNMSIpAddr.description: The IP address of the primary Network Management Station. It is to this address that Traps and TFTP requests will be directed.

nodeState.name: nodeState
nodeState.description: The state of the switch. The switch needs to await the state to be set to active before being fully operational after cold boot, when the NMS is reachable.

nodePollStatus.name: nodePollStatus
nodePollStatus.description: The consolidated node status in response to keep-alive polls. It is an octet string of a proprietary format

nodeModel.name: nodeModel
nodeModel.description: The part number of the node.

nodeSerial.name: nodeSerial
nodeSerial.description: The serial number (i.e., Ethernet Addr) of the switch.

nodeCpuUtil.name: nodeCpuUtil
nodeCpuUtil.description: The CPU utilization percentage for packet processing.

nodePsAStatus.name: nodePsAStatus
nodePsAStatus.description: The status of the power supply A. For a detailed explanation for the power supply being either in the down or marginal state, refer to the nodePsADiagCode object.

nodePsBStatus.name: nodePsBStatus
nodePsBStatus.description: The status of the power supply B. For a detailed explanation for the power supply being either in the down or marginal state, refer to the nodePsBDiagCode object.

nodeFanEntry.name: nodeFanEntry
nodeFanEntry.description: A Fan entry contains the status of a fan.

nodeFanIndex.name: nodeFanIndex
nodeFanIndex.description: A unique value for each fan.

nodeFanSpeed.name: nodeFanSpeed
nodeFanSpeed.description: The speed in Revolutions Per. Minute (RPM) of the fan.

nodeMemoryUtil.name: nodeMemoryUtil
nodeMemoryUtil.description: The percentage of system memory utilization on this intelligent card.

nodeMemoryUsage.name: nodeMemoryUsage
nodeMemoryUsage.description: The system memory utilization, in terms of free bytes, for this intelligent card.

nodeMaxFramesize.name: nodeMaxFramesize
nodeMaxFramesize.description: The maximum frame size supported by the node. The default is 4096.

nodeQOSPollTimer.name: nodeQOSPollTimer
nodeQOSPollTimer.description: The timer (seconds) for generating QOS polling packets.

nodeActivePvcs.name: nodeActivePvcs
nodeActivePvcs.description: The number of currently active PVCs on the node.

nodeInactivePvcs.name: nodeInactivePvcs
nodeInactivePvcs.description: The number of currently inactive PVCs on the node.

nodePendingPvcs.name: nodePendingPvcs
nodePendingPvcs.description: The number of currently call pending PVCs on the node.

nodeInOctets.name: nodeInOctets
nodeInOctets.description: The total number of octets received on the node, including framing bytes.

nodeInPkts.name: nodeInPkts
nodeInPkts.description: The total number of packets received on the node.

nodeOutOctets.name: nodeOutOctets
nodeOutOctets.description: The total number of octets transmitted out of the node, including framing bytes.

nodeOutPkts.name: nodeOutPkts
nodeOutPkts.description: The total number of packets requested to be transmitted out of the node, including those that were discarded or not sent.

nodeSwFilename.name: nodeSwFilename
nodeSwFilename.description: Name of the file to be downloaded.

nodeRebootAfterLoad.name: nodeRebootAfterLoad
nodeRebootAfterLoad.description: Instructs the device to either automatically reboot after the successful scheduled download or not.

nodeSwToLoad.name: nodeSwToLoad
nodeSwToLoad.description: Instructs the device to initiate a software download (via tftp) request to the master management station after the specified time ticks have elapsed.

nodeSwLoadState.name: nodeSwLoadState
nodeSwLoadState.description: The state of the software download request. A download which is in either the PENDING, ACTIVE or FAILED state can be terminated by setting this object to INACTIVE.

nodePrFilename.name: nodePrFilename
nodePrFilename.description: Name of the PRAM image file to be downloaded.

nodePrToLoad.name: nodePrToLoad
nodePrToLoad.description: Instructs the device to initiate a PRAM image file download (via tftp) request to the master management station after the specified time ticks have elapsed.

nodePrLoadState.name: nodePrLoadState
nodePrLoadState.description: The state of the PRAM download request. A download which is in either the PENDING, ACTIVE or FAILED state can be terminated by setting this object to INACTIVE.

nodeToWarmboot.name: nodeToWarmboot
nodeToWarmboot.description: Instructs the switch to initiate a system warm boot after the specified time ticks have elapsed. A value of 0 indicates cancellation of the previously scheduled re-boot request.

nodeToColdboot.name: nodeToColdboot
nodeToColdboot.description: Instructs the switch to initiate a system cold boot after the specified time ticks have elapsed. A value of 0 indicates cancellation of the previously scheduled re-boot request.

nodeToRedundant.name: nodeToRedundant
nodeToRedundant.description: If redundancy is configured, instructs the node acting as Backup to disable the Active node and take over as the Active node. The disabling is initiated after the specified time ticks have elapsed. A value of 0 indicates cancellation of the previously scheduled request.

nodeInitiateBulkStats.name: nodeInitiateBulkStats
nodeInitiateBulkStats.description: Initiates a Bulk Statistics poll and via TFTP, transfer the data to the specified IP address.

nodeDiagNonFatalSource.name: nodeDiagNonFatalSource
nodeDiagNonFatalSource.description: Source who reported last non-fatal error.

nodeDiagNonFatalTime.name: nodeDiagNonFatalTime
nodeDiagNonFatalTime.description: Time the last non-fatal error was reported.

nodeDiagNonFatalErrMajor.name: nodeDiagNonFatalErrMajor
nodeDiagNonFatalErrMajor.description: Major error code of last non-fatal error.

nodeDiagNonFatalErrMinor.name: nodeDiagNonFatalErrMinor
nodeDiagNonFatalErrMinor.description: Minor error code of last non-fatal error.

nodeDiagNonFatalStr.name: nodeDiagNonFatalStr
nodeDiagNonFatalStr.description: Ascii string describing last non-fatal error.

nodeDiagFatalSource.name: nodeDiagFatalSource
nodeDiagFatalSource.description: Source who reported last fatal error.

nodeDiagFatalTime.name: nodeDiagFatalTime
nodeDiagFatalTime.description: Time the last fatal error was reported.

nodeDiagFatalErrMajor.name: nodeDiagFatalErrMajor
nodeDiagFatalErrMajor.description: Major error code of last fatal error.

nodeDiagFatalErrMinor.name: nodeDiagFatalErrMinor
nodeDiagFatalErrMinor.description: Minor error code of last fatal error.

nodeDiagFatalStr.name: nodeDiagFatalStr
nodeDiagFatalStr.description: Ascii string describing last fatal error.

nodeDiagFatalReboots.name: nodeDiagFatalReboots
nodeDiagFatalReboots.description: Number of times the switch has re-booted since last fatal error was reported.

nodeDiagFatalAddress.name: nodeDiagFatalAddress
nodeDiagFatalAddress.description: Address switch was executing when it encountered fatal error.

nodeDiagBackgroundPasses.name: nodeDiagBackgroundPasses
nodeDiagBackgroundPasses.description: Number of passes made by the background diagnostics.

nodeDiagBackgroundFailures.name: nodeDiagBackgroundFailures
nodeDiagBackgroundFailures.description: Number of failures discovered by background diagnostics.

nodeDiagBackgroundSuccesses.name: nodeDiagBackgroundSuccesses
nodeDiagBackgroundSuccesses.description: Number of successful passes by background diagnostics.

nodeDiagLEDReset.name: nodeDiagLEDReset
nodeDiagLEDReset.description: Change the node state from marginal to active. Change the LED from yellow to green.

nodeDiagPowerExtensive.name: nodeDiagPowerExtensive
nodeDiagPowerExtensive.description: Should power on diagnostics do slower, extensive testing, or fast testing?

nodePortPoll.name: nodePortPoll
nodePortPoll.description: The consolidated port status in response to keep-alive polls.

nodeMaxTelnetConsole.name: nodeMaxTelnetConsole
nodeMaxTelnetConsole.description: The number of concurrent telnet consoles allowed. The default is 2. The maximum is 5. Set it 0 to disable telnet access.

nodeConsoleTimeout.name: nodeConsoleTimeout
nodeConsoleTimeout.description: Idle-logoff timer in minutes. The default is 5 minutes, and the maximum can be set is 60 minutes. To disable idle-logout, set this to 0.

nodeConsoleTable.name: nodeConsoleTable
nodeConsoleTable.description: A list of active consoles on the node, logged in through telnet or serial port.

nodeConsoleIndex.name: nodeConsoleIndex
nodeConsoleIndex.description: A positive integer to identify a console

nodeUserName.name: nodeUserName
nodeUserName.description: The login user name up to 31 characters. There is no validation of the name, i.e., any string is acceptable.

nodeUserFrom.name: nodeUserFrom
nodeUserFrom.description: The IP address from which the user logged in. 0.0.0.0 if the user logged in through serial port.

nodeConsoleAccessMode.name: nodeConsoleAccessMode
nodeConsoleAccessMode.description: The access mode of the console. By default, a user is in READ ONLY mode.

nodeConsoleUptime.name: nodeConsoleUptime
nodeConsoleUptime.description: How long the console has been active.

nodePsADiagCode.name: nodePsADiagCode
nodePsADiagCode.description: The failure code of the power supply A. A non-zero value indicates one or more failures. Refer to the hardware manual for a description of the failure code.

nodePsBDiagCode.name: nodePsBDiagCode
nodePsBDiagCode.description: The failure code of the power supply B. A non-zero value indicates one or more failures. Refer to the hardware manual for a description of the failure code.

nodeFrameMemoryUtil.name: nodeFrameMemoryUtil
nodeFrameMemoryUtil.description: The percentage of frame memory utilization on this intelligent card.

nodeFrameMemoryUsage.name: nodeFrameMemoryUsage
nodeFrameMemoryUsage.description: The frame memory utilization, in terms of free bytes, for this intelligent card.

nodeSvcLastCallFailure.name: nodeSvcLastCallFailure
nodeSvcLastCallFailure.description: A textual string describing the last call failure.

nodeRerouteDelay.name: nodeRerouteDelay
nodeRerouteDelay.description: The number of seconds delay between each reroute batch event.

nodeRerouteCount.name: nodeRerouteCount
nodeRerouteCount.description: The number of virtual circuits to request a reroute for duing a single reroute batch event.

nodeFileTransferRequest.name: nodeFileTransferRequest
nodeFileTransferRequest.description: This object is used to initiate file transfers to and from the switch. A management station can initiate a file transfer by settting this object of text string in the following format: operation filename time-to-wait target-host protocol where operation - [get | put], filename - configuration.[card] time-to-wait - a number in seconds target-host - the IP address of target host protocol - [tftp | ftp] Multiple transfers can be specified by repeating above with ';' between each transfer specifier. Examples: o get configuration.10 5 152.148.10.100 tftp will start a transfer of configuration information on card 10 to host 152.148.10.100 in 5 seconds. o put configuration.1 2 152.148.1.1 tftp ; get configuration.1 15 152.148.1.1 tftp will (1) transfer configuration.1 from 152.148.1.1 (2) transfer configuration.2 to 152.148.1.1 To cancel the transfer request, set this object to empty.

nodeFileTransferStatus.name: nodeFileTransferStatus
nodeFileTransferStatus.description: The status of the file tarnsfer.

nodeTime.name: nodeTime
nodeTime.description: The current wall-clock time that is set on the switch in Universal Coordinated Time (UCT). The value is the number of seconds since 00:00:00 UCT January 1, 1970.

nodeBillingAPAddress.name: nodeBillingAPAddress
nodeBillingAPAddress.description: The IP Address of the Adjunct Billing Processor that is servicing this switch.

nodeBillingAPUsername.name: nodeBillingAPUsername
nodeBillingAPUsername.description: The Username of the account on the Adjunct Billing Processor to which usage data will be transferred via FTP.

nodeBillingAPPassword.name: nodeBillingAPPassword
nodeBillingAPPassword.description: The Password corresponding to the account identified by nodeBillingAPUsername. A NULL string is returned when read.

nodeBillingSwAPCommsFailures.name: nodeBillingSwAPCommsFailures
nodeBillingSwAPCommsFailures.description: The number of times that communication from the switch to the Adjunct Billing Processor has failed during the current aggregation period. A failure signifies failure of a file transfer operation to the Adjunct Processor.

nodeBillingTable.name: nodeBillingTable
nodeBillingTable.description: A table of Billing System managable objects, indexed by service.

nodeBillingEntry.name: nodeBillingEntry
nodeBillingEntry.description: A nodeBillingEntry contains a set of statistics that summarize the Billing System performance for a particular service.

nodeBillingService.name: nodeBillingService
nodeBillingService.description: The service being reported. This is the index into the table. Additional table rows for Frame Relay and ATM may be provided in the future.

nodeBilling.name: nodeBilling
nodeBilling.description: Switch to enable and disable billing on the STDX. When the value of nodeBilling is 'enabled', the value of a logical port's lportBilling object will take precedence. When the value of nodeBilling is 'disabled', it overrides all logical ports' lportBilling objects and billing is disabled across the entire switch. The default value of this object is 'disabled'.

nodeBillingAggrPeriod.name: nodeBillingAggrPeriod
nodeBillingAggrPeriod.description: Defines the length of the Billing Aggregation Period in seconds. The default value is 15 minutes. The minimum value is 10 minutes.

nodeBillingCurAggrPeriodStart.name: nodeBillingCurAggrPeriodStart
nodeBillingCurAggrPeriodStart.description: The start-time of the current aggregation period, given by the number of seconds since 00:00:00 UCT January 1, 1970.

nodeBillingCurAggrPeriodEnd.name: nodeBillingCurAggrPeriodEnd
nodeBillingCurAggrPeriodEnd.description: The end-time of the current aggregation period, given by the number of seconds since 00:00:00 UCT January 1, 1970.

nodeBillingCollection.name: nodeBillingCollection
nodeBillingCollection.description: Defines how often the Data Aggregation process on the CP is to poll the IOPs for usage data. The default value is 30 second. The range is unbounded, but practical use will dictate a range from 30 seconds to 1 minute.

nodeBillingDailyProcessing.name: nodeBillingDailyProcessing
nodeBillingDailyProcessing.description: Defines whether the Billing System is to perform a set of carrier-specific actions at the time given by nodeBillingDPTime. This object can be used to schedule the generation of statistics on a 24-hour basis, for example.

nodeBillingDPTime.name: nodeBillingDPTime
nodeBillingDPTime.description: Defines the time (given by the number of seconds since 00:00:00 UCT) that the Billing System is to perform a set of carrier-specific actions. This object can be used to schedule the generation of statistics on a 24-hour basis, for example.

nodeBillingUsageRecOvflWarnings.name: nodeBillingUsageRecOvflWarnings
nodeBillingUsageRecOvflWarnings.description: Count of the number of usage record counter-value overflow conditions that have occurred during the current aggregation period. An overflow condition exists when an attempt was made to update a usage record counter, but such an update would have overflowed the counter. In this case, the usage record is closed and a new one is opened, if there is sufficient space in the service's aggregated usage data store.

nodeBillingTotalUsageRecOvflWarnings.name: nodeBillingTotalUsageRecOvflWarnings
nodeBillingTotalUsageRecOvflWarnings.description: Count of the number of usage record overflow conditions that have occurred during the current day.

nodeBillingBillableUsageEvents.name: nodeBillingBillableUsageEvents
nodeBillingBillableUsageEvents.description: Count of the number of data units (e.g, SMDS L3 PDUs) processed for billing treatment.

nodeBillingNonBillableUsageEvents.name: nodeBillingNonBillableUsageEvents
nodeBillingNonBillableUsageEvents.description: Count of the number of data units (e.g, SMDS L3 PDUs) not considered for billing treatment.

nodeBillingUsageRecCreated.name: nodeBillingUsageRecCreated
nodeBillingUsageRecCreated.description: Count of the number of usage records created during the current aggregation period.

nodeBillingTotalUsageRecCreated.name: nodeBillingTotalUsageRecCreated
nodeBillingTotalUsageRecCreated.description: Count of the total number of usage records created during the current day.

nodeBillingUsageRecCrFailures.name: nodeBillingUsageRecCrFailures
nodeBillingUsageRecCrFailures.description: Total number of usage records that could not be created during the current aggregation period. This counter is normally incremented when the usage data file is at capacity and no additional usage records can be added.

nodeBillingTotalUsageRecCrFailures.name: nodeBillingTotalUsageRecCrFailures
nodeBillingTotalUsageRecCrFailures.description: Total number of usage records that could not be created during the current day.

nodeBillingUsageRecSent.name: nodeBillingUsageRecSent
nodeBillingUsageRecSent.description: Total number of usage records that have been transferred to the Adjunct Billing Processor during the current aggregation period.

nodeBillingTotalUsageRecSent.name: nodeBillingTotalUsageRecSent
nodeBillingTotalUsageRecSent.description: Total number of usage records that have been transferred to the Adjunct Billing Processor during the current day.

nodeBillingUsageDataStoreFull.name: nodeBillingUsageDataStoreFull
nodeBillingUsageDataStoreFull.description: The number of times the aggregated usage data store became full during the current aggregation period.

nodeBillingTotalUsageDataStoreFull.name: nodeBillingTotalUsageDataStoreFull
nodeBillingTotalUsageDataStoreFull.description: Total number of times the aggregated usage data store became full during the current day.

nodeBillingAdminAction.name: nodeBillingAdminAction
nodeBillingAdminAction.description: This object defines a set of administrative actions that can be performed by the Billing System. forceUpload - Forces the current aggregation period to end and the service's aggregated usage data file to be uploaded to the Adjunct Processor. A new aggregation period is then started. This action can be requested when billing is enabled or disabled for the service. This object always returns invalid(1) when read.

nodeRerouteAlg.name: nodeRerouteAlg
nodeRerouteAlg.description: The number of seconds delay between each reroute batch event.

nodeOamAlarmDisabled.name: nodeOamAlarmDisabled
nodeOamAlarmDisabled.description: If disabled then don't generate oam alarms for circuits that are down on this switch.

nodeRefclocksrcTable.name: nodeRefclocksrcTable
nodeRefclocksrcTable.description: A list of generators (sources) for the system reference clock on the node. This reference clock is used by the clock generation unit (CGU) to create the system clock. To this reference clock the constant bit rate ATM interface cards (CBR cards) are synchronized.

nodeRefclocksrcEntry.name: nodeRefclocksrcEntry
nodeRefclocksrcEntry.description: Information of a single system reference clock source.

nodeRefclocksrcIndex.name: nodeRefclocksrcIndex
nodeRefclocksrcIndex.description: A positive integer to identify an entry in the nodeRefclocksrcTable.

nodeRefclocksrcPriority.name: nodeRefclocksrcPriority
nodeRefclocksrcPriority.description: The priority of the system reference clock source. A source with a nodeRefclocksrcPriority=n means that this source is used before a source with a higher value of nodeRefclocksrcPriority as long as this source is available. The system choses one of the sources with the same lowest available value of nodeRefclocksrcPriority.

nodeRefclocksrcType.name: nodeRefclocksrcType
nodeRefclocksrcType.description: The type of the reference clock source. It is either an external clock source connected to a ATM-IWU or DS3 card, or the reference clock is recovered from the line interface.

nodeRefclocksrcSlotId.name: nodeRefclocksrcSlotId
nodeRefclocksrcSlotId.description: The card number of the reference clock source. In case of an external clock interface this is the number of the card as defined in cardLogicalSlotId. In case of a clock recovered from the line interface it is the number of the corresponding card as defined in cardLogicalSlotId.

nodeRefclocksrcPportId.name: nodeRefclocksrcPportId
nodeRefclocksrcPportId.description: The interface number of the reference clock source. In case of an external clock interface this is meaningless. In case of a clock recovered from the line interface it is the number of the corresponding pport as defined in pportId.

nodeRefclockActiveSrc.name: nodeRefclockActiveSrc
nodeRefclockActiveSrc.description: The entry number of the active reference clock source in nodeRefclocksrcTable. If zero, the CGU is in free-running mode or holdover mode using the last PLL parameters.

nodeRefclockActiveCGUSlotId.name: nodeRefclockActiveCGUSlotId
nodeRefclockActiveCGUSlotId.description: The physical slot id of the current master CGU board.

nodeRefclockActiveCGUMode.name: nodeRefclockActiveCGUMode
nodeRefclockActiveCGUMode.description: The clock mode of the current master CGU board.

nodeInitiateImageBackup.name: nodeInitiateImageBackup
nodeInitiateImageBackup.description: When set, copy all of the runtime application images and configuration images to there corresponding backup locations on the hard disk.

nodeImageBackupState.name: nodeImageBackupState
nodeImageBackupState.description: Provides the current state of the images backup operation.

nodeInitiateImageRestore.name: nodeInitiateImageRestore
nodeInitiateImageRestore.description: When set, copy all of the runtime application images and configuration images from their BACKUP locations on the hard disk to there corresponding ACTIVE locations on the hard disk. Once completed, reboot the entire node.

nodeApplicationTable.name: nodeApplicationTable
nodeApplicationTable.description: A list of Application Image Descriptions.

nodeApplicationEntry.name: nodeApplicationEntry
nodeApplicationEntry.description: An Application Entry contains a description of the application image, the version of the PRIMARY copy and the version of the SECONDARY copy.

nodeApplicationIndex.name: nodeApplicationIndex
nodeApplicationIndex.description: The numeric index of application images. 1 - SP Runtime Application 2 - IOM Type A Runtime Application 3 - IOM Type B Runtime Application 4 - IOM Type C Runtime Application 5 - IOM Type D Runtime Application

nodeApplicationDescription.name: nodeApplicationDescription
nodeApplicationDescription.description: The description of this Application Image.

nodePrimaryVersion.name: nodePrimaryVersion
nodePrimaryVersion.description: The version of the PRIMARY Application Image.

nodeSecondaryVersion.name: nodeSecondaryVersion
nodeSecondaryVersion.description: The version of the SECONDARY Application Image.

nodePrimarySyncRefAdminState.name: nodePrimarySyncRefAdminState
nodePrimarySyncRefAdminState.description: The requested primary clock synchronization reference source.

nodePrimarySyncRefOperationalState.name: nodePrimarySyncRefOperationalState
nodePrimarySyncRefOperationalState.description: The actual primary clock synchronization reference source.

nodeSecondarySyncRefAdminState.name: nodeSecondarySyncRefAdminState
nodeSecondarySyncRefAdminState.description: The requested secondary clock synchronization reference source.

nodeSecondarySyncRefOperationalState.name: nodeSecondarySyncRefOperationalState
nodeSecondarySyncRefOperationalState.description: The actual secondary clock synchronization reference source.

nodePrimaryPLLOperationalState.name: nodePrimaryPLLOperationalState
nodePrimaryPLLOperationalState.description: The current state of the primary synchronization PLL.

nodeSecondaryPLLOperationalState.name: nodeSecondaryPLLOperationalState
nodeSecondaryPLLOperationalState.description: The current state of the secondary synchronization PLL.

nodeExternalClockAOperationalState.name: nodeExternalClockAOperationalState
nodeExternalClockAOperationalState.description: The current state of the External Clock A reference.

nodeExternalClockBOperationalState.name: nodeExternalClockBOperationalState
nodeExternalClockBOperationalState.description: The current state of the External Clock B reference.

nodePortClockAOperationalState.name: nodePortClockAOperationalState
nodePortClockAOperationalState.description: The current state of the Port Clock A reference.

nodePortClockBOperationalState.name: nodePortClockBOperationalState
nodePortClockBOperationalState.description: The current state of the Port Clock B reference.

nodeExternalTimingSource.name: nodeExternalTimingSource
nodeExternalTimingSource.description: The reference for the external timing output.

nodeSyncAutoRestore.name: nodeSyncAutoRestore
nodeSyncAutoRestore.description: The configuration of the Synchronization Reference Auto Restoration function.

nodeExternalClockInterfaceType.name: nodeExternalClockInterfaceType
nodeExternalClockInterfaceType.description: The interface type of the External Clock references.

cardNumber.name: cardNumber
cardNumber.description: The number of manageable cards physically present in this node. Standby cards are not considered manageable.

cardTable.name: cardTable
cardTable.description: A list of cardEntry's. The number of entries is given by the value of cardNumber

cardEntry.name: cardEntry
cardEntry.description: The card entry contains objects relevant to managing intelligent cards.

cardLogicalSlotId.name: cardLogicalSlotId
cardLogicalSlotId.description: The logical slot number of this card. This is used as an index for the cardTable. In redundant configurations, this can be the physical slot number of either redundant card. In non redundant configurations, this is the same as cardPhysicalSlotId.

cardPhysicalSlotId.name: cardPhysicalSlotId
cardPhysicalSlotId.description: The physical slot number of this card. This can be different from cardLogicalSlotId in redundant configurations.

cardAdminStatus.name: cardAdminStatus
cardAdminStatus.description: The desired status of this card.

cardOperStatus.name: cardOperStatus
cardOperStatus.description: The current status of this card.

cardDiagStatus.name: cardDiagStatus
cardDiagStatus.description: The current diagnostics status of this card, as determined by background diagnostics.

cardRedundConfig.name: cardRedundConfig
cardRedundConfig.description: Is the card configured for redundancy?

cardRedundSlotMask.name: cardRedundSlotMask
cardRedundSlotMask.description: A 32-bit mask indicating the slot position of this card and its redundant partner. The low bit is slot 1 and the high bit is slot 32.

cardRedundActual.name: cardRedundActual
cardRedundActual.description: Is the card currently connected to a redundant card?

cardRedundState.name: cardRedundState
cardRedundState.description: The current redundancy state of this card. Exception: when used as an index for the following objects: cardAdminType, cardAdminCapability, and cardAdminStatus, the value 1 indicates the card of the redundant pair in the lower-numbered slot, and the value 2 indicates the card in the higher-numbered slot.

cardToRedundant.name: cardToRedundant
cardToRedundant.description: Instructs the standby card to reset the active card and take over as new active card. The reset takes place after specified time ticks have elapsed. A value of 0 indicates cancellation of the previously scheduled request.

cardDiagNonFatalSource.name: cardDiagNonFatalSource
cardDiagNonFatalSource.description: Source who reported last non-fatal error.

cardDiagNonFatalTime.name: cardDiagNonFatalTime
cardDiagNonFatalTime.description: Time the last non-fatal error was reported.

cardDiagNonFatalErrMajor.name: cardDiagNonFatalErrMajor
cardDiagNonFatalErrMajor.description: Major error code of last non-fatal error.

cardDiagNonFatalErrMinor.name: cardDiagNonFatalErrMinor
cardDiagNonFatalErrMinor.description: Minor error code of last non-fatal error.

cardDiagNonFatalStr.name: cardDiagNonFatalStr
cardDiagNonFatalStr.description: Ascii string describing last non-fatal error.

cardDiagFatalSource.name: cardDiagFatalSource
cardDiagFatalSource.description: Source who reported last fatal error.

cardDiagFatalTime.name: cardDiagFatalTime
cardDiagFatalTime.description: Time the last fatal error was reported.

cardDiagFatalErrMajor.name: cardDiagFatalErrMajor
cardDiagFatalErrMajor.description: Major error code of last fatal error.

cardDiagFatalErrMinor.name: cardDiagFatalErrMinor
cardDiagFatalErrMinor.description: Minor error code of last fatal error.

cardDiagFatalStr.name: cardDiagFatalStr
cardDiagFatalStr.description: Ascii string describing last fatal error.

cardDiagFatalReboots.name: cardDiagFatalReboots
cardDiagFatalReboots.description: Number of times the switch has re-booted since last fatal error was reported.

cardDiagFatalAddress.name: cardDiagFatalAddress
cardDiagFatalAddress.description: Address switch was executing when it encountered fatal error.

cardDiagBackgroundPasses.name: cardDiagBackgroundPasses

cardCktGroupTrap.name: cardCktGroupTrap
cardCktGroupTrap.description: This is a ( 4 + n*134 ) byte octet string where n => 1. The first and second byte is the interface/slot id of the link/IOP going down or link goes up. The third byte is the reason why circuits go down: 1 is a user link goes down, 2 is a trunk link goes down, 3 is an IOP goes down and 4 is an user link goes up The fourth byte is the count of entries in the following circuit bit map array. Each circuit bit map entry is 134 bytes. The first 2 bytes is the IOP slot on which dlci's are defined. The second 2 bytes is the Physical port ID on which dlci's are defined. The third 2 bytes is the interface id on which dlci's are defined. The following 128 bytes (1024 bits) is a bit map for dlci's defined on the interface. The left-most bit of the first byte represent dlci 0 and the right-most bit of the 128th byte represent dlci 1023. If a bit is set, it means the corresponding dlci on that interface is up/down.

pportISDNChannelStatus.name: pportISDNChannelStatus
pportISDNChannelStatus.description: The ISDN call status of all the B-Channels on the pport are encoded into this 24 character, (for T1 ISDN PRI card...23B+D) or 31 character, (for E1 ISDN PRI card...30B+D ) ASCII string. The respective call state for each B-Channel is represented in its corresponding bit position. The D-Channel status is similarly encoded into the appropriate bit position (24th for T1) or (16th for E1). The encoding legend is as follows... I B-Channel is in Idle state R B-Channel is in Dialing (Ringing) state C B-Channel is in Connected (Active) state H B-Channel is in Releasing (Hanging-up) state U D-Channel is Up D D-Channel is Down

pportAAL5CRC32Error.description: Number of received AAL5 packets with CRC32 errors.

pportAPSpairedSlotId.name: pportAPSpairedSlotId
pportAPSpairedSlotId.description: Slot ID of the paired-with APS pport. Writable only when pportRedundancyArch is disabled.

pportAPSpairedPportId.name: pportAPSpairedPportId
pportAPSpairedPportId.description: Pport ID of the paired-with APS pport. Writable only when pportRedundancyARch is disabled.

pportAPSsfBerThresh.name: pportAPSsfBerThresh
pportAPSsfBerThresh.description: Exponent N for APS Signal Failure based on BER. A line bit-error-rate above 10^-N causes an SF BER failure to be asserted. SF BER is cleared when the line BER returns to less than 10^-7.

pportAPSsdBerThresh.name: pportAPSsdBerThresh
pportAPSsdBerThresh.description: Exponent N for APS Signal Degrade based on BER. A line bit-error-rate above 10^-N causes an SD BER failure to be asserted. SD BER is cleared when the line BER returns to less than 10^-(N+1).

pportAPSwtrPeriod.name: pportAPSwtrPeriod

pportAPSprotectionLineState.name: pportAPSprotectionLineState

pportAPSxCommand.name: pportAPSxCommand
pportAPSxCommand.description: External switch commands. The clear command clears any previously activated external command. Manual switch is preemptable by auto-switch-requests (line failures) while forced switch is not preemptable (except if the protection line fails). Manual and forced switch from protection to working, is valid only for 1+1 mode. Exercise simulates a switchover using APS signalling without actually performing a switch to protection line.

pportAPSconfigStatus.name: pportAPSconfigStatus
pportAPSconfigStatus.description: Status of APS pport configuration. The not-configured status indicates the pport APS feature is not configured or it is a non-APS pport. The valid state indicates the pport APS function is configured and has been validated by the APS manager. The invalid state indicates that the APS manager has detected a conflict between the working line and protection line pport configurations. The user must clear the invalid state by changing the configuration of the misconfigured pport as soon as possible. Check pportAPSadminDir, pportAPSlineType, pportAPSrevertiveMode, and pportAPSwtrPeriod for any misconfigurations.

pportAPSOperRxStatus.name: pportAPSOperRxStatus

pportATMTcaInHECErrorUAlertPeriod.description: ATM tca ingress HEC error uncorrectable alert period (in min.).

pportATMTcaInHECErrorUThresh.name: pportATMTcaInHECErrorUThresh
pportATMTcaInHECErrorUThresh.description: ATM tca ingress HEC error uncorrectable threshold.

pportATMTcaEBufOverflowCBRAlertPeriod.name: pportATMTcaEBufOverflowCBRAlertPeriod
pportATMTcaEBufOverflowCBRAlertPeriod.description: ATM tca egress buffer overflow CBR Alert period (in min)

pportATMTcaEBufOverflowCBRThresh.name: pportATMTcaEBufOverflowCBRThresh
pportATMTcaEBufOverflowCBRThresh.description: ATM tca egress buffer overflow CBR threshold.

pportATMTcaEBufOverflowABRAlertPeriod.name: pportATMTcaEBufOverflowABRAlertPeriod
pportATMTcaEBufOverflowABRAlertPeriod.description: ATM tca egress buffer overflow ABR alert period (in min)

pportATMTcaEBufOverflowABRThresh.name: pportATMTcaEBufOverflowABRThresh
pportATMTcaEBufOverflowABRThresh.description: ATM tca egress buffer overflow ABR threshold.

pportATMTcaEBufOverflowVBR1AlertPeriod.name: pportATMTcaEBufOverflowVBR1AlertPeriod
pportATMTcaEBufOverflowVBR1AlertPeriod.description: ATM tca egress buffer overflow VBR1 alert period (in min)

pportATMTcaEBufOverflowVBR1Thresh.name: pportATMTcaEBufOverflowVBR1Thresh
pportATMTcaEBufOverflowVBR1Thresh.description: ATM tca egress buffer overflow VBR1 threshold.

pportATMTcaEBufOverflowVBR2AlertPeriod.name: pportATMTcaEBufOverflowVBR2AlertPeriod
pportATMTcaEBufOverflowVBR2AlertPeriod.description: ATM tca egress buffer overflow VBR2 alert period (in min)

pportATMTcaEBufOverflowVBR2Thresh.name: pportATMTcaEBufOverflowVBR2Thresh
pportATMTcaEBufOverflowVBR2Thresh.description: ATM tca egress buffer overflow VBR2 threshold.

pportATMTcaInFramerFIFOOverflowAlertPeri.name: pportATMTcaInFramerFIFOOverflowAlertPeriod
pportATMTcaInFramerFIFOOverflowAlertPeri.description: ATM tca ingress framer FIFO overflow alert period (in min)

pportATMTcaInFramerFIFOOverflowThresh.name: pportATMTcaInFramerFIFOOverflowThresh
pportATMTcaInFramerFIFOOverflowThresh.description: ATM tca ingress framer FIFO overflow threshold.

pportATMTcaELookupFailureAlertPeriod.name: pportATMTcaELookupFailureAlertPeriod
pportATMTcaELookupFailureAlertPeriod.description: ATM tca egress lookup failure alert period (in min)

pportATMTcaELookupFailureThresh.name: pportATMTcaELookupFailureThresh
pportATMTcaELookupFailureThresh.description: ATM tca egress lookup failure threshold.

pportATMTcaId.name: pportATMTcaId
pportATMTcaId.description: This object identifies the the most recently declared pport ATM threshold crossing alert

pportFethAdminMacAddr.name: pportFethAdminMacAddr
pportFethAdminMacAddr.description: The configured MAC address to use for this Fast Ethernet port. Setting this to all zeros will force the port to use the burned in MAC address.

pportFethOperMacAddr.name: pportFethOperMacAddr
pportFethOperMacAddr.description: The actual MAC address in use for this Fast Ethernet port.

pportConfigAlarmSoakTime.name: pportConfigAlarmSoakTime
pportConfigAlarmSoakTime.description: This is the soak time for configurable alarms. An alarm of this type must persist for this period before it is declared. The time is specified in millseconds units.

pportConfigAlarmClearTime.name: pportConfigAlarmClearTime
pportConfigAlarmClearTime.description: This is the soak time for configurable alarms. An alarm of this type must remain clear for this period before it is declared to be cleared. The time is specified in millseconds units.

pportFethPortCapability.name: pportFethPortCapability
pportFethPortCapability.description: Selection for the speed (10/100) and mode (half/full duplex) of operation for Fast Ethernet ports.

pportVpshapingDiscardCellCount.name: pportVpshapingDiscardCellCount
pportVpshapingDiscardCellCount.description: Cells discarded due to buffer overflow on this pport because of traffic shaping.

pportTrafficShaperTable.name: pportTrafficShaperTable
pportTrafficShaperTable.description: A list of Parameters assigned to the 16 traffic shaper parameter conbinations of each pport of the ATM-IWU.

pportTrafficShaperEntry.name: pportTrafficShaperEntry
pportTrafficShaperEntry.description: Information of a single system reference clock source.

pportTrafficShaperIndex.name: pportTrafficShaperIndex
pportTrafficShaperIndex.description: A positive integer to identify an entry in the pportTrafficShaperTable. The ATM-IWU and CS cards support exactly 16 shapers.

pportTrafficShaperPriority.name: pportTrafficShaperPriority
pportTrafficShaperPriority.description: The priority of the Shaper. Channels tied to a Shaper are served only if no higher priority Shapers await service. 0 ist the highest, 15 the lowest priority.

pportTrafficShaperCellRatioDividend.name: pportTrafficShaperCellRatioDividend
pportTrafficShaperCellRatioDividend.description: The quotient of pportTrafficShaperCellRatioDividend and pportTrafficShaperCellRatioDivisor determines the average rate allocated to the shaper. The shaper serves portTrafficShaperCellRatioDividend cells in pportTrafficShaperCellRatioDivisor cell times.

pportTrafficShaperPeak.name: pportTrafficShaperPeak
pportTrafficShaperPeak.description: The peak cell rate. It defines the minimum gap (in cell units) between emission of any consecutive cells in this channel.

pportTrafficShaperCredit.name: pportTrafficShaperCredit
pportTrafficShaperCredit.description: Defines the maximum number of credits that can be accumulated by a shaper. This is equivalent to the maximum burst allowed at the peak rate.

lportTable.name: lportTable
lportTable.description: A list of logical port entries. The number of entries is given by the value of ifNumber in MIB-II.

lportEntry.name: lportEntry
lportEntry.description: The logical port entry contains objects relevant to a logical port.

lportIfIndex.name: lportIfIndex
lportIfIndex.description: The ifIndex value of the corresponding ifEntry.

lportSlotId.name: lportSlotId
lportSlotId.description: The slot number of the board the port is on.

lportPportId.name: lportPportId
lportPportId.description: The physical port number of the interface on the board.

lportId.name: lportId
lportId.description: The logical port number of the interface on the physical port. A logical port can be uniquely identified in a Cascade network as { NodeId.lportSlotId.lportPportId.lportId }. lportId is defaulted to 1 (i.e., one-to-one mapping between the physical port and the logical port such as local V.35 or carrier) except the following cases: - For ufr, nfr and trk logical port, it indicates the bundle number for fractional T1 or 24-bundle T1. - For pdntrk logical port, it indicates the dlci over the PDN. Note that pdntrk is not allowed on fractional T1 or 24-bundle T1 physical port.

lportLink.name: lportLink
lportLink.description: The equipment type of the peer to which the logical port is connected.

lportProtocol.name: lportProtocol
lportProtocol.description: The data link protocol running on the logical port.

lportSignal.name: lportSignal
lportSignal.description: The user-network signalling capability for SVC and DLCMI of the logical port. Note that this only applies to fr protocol port.

lportFt1Ds0s.name: lportFt1Ds0s
lportFt1Ds0s.description: The bit mask indicating the DS0s for the fractional T1/E1 logical port which must be a subset of the corresponding pportDs1Ds0s. It's represented by a 32-bit hex char string.

lportGlobalDlci.name: lportGlobalDlci
lportGlobalDlci.description: The global DLCI correspondent to the interface if the DLCI is globally significant in the network. Note that this object is read-write only during creation, and read-only after creation.

lportDlcmiStd.name: lportDlcmiStd
lportDlcmiStd.description: This variable states which Data Link Connection Management scheme is active (and by implication, what DLCI it uses) on the Frame Relay interface.

lportDlciAddrFmt.name: lportDlciAddrFmt
lportDlciAddrFmt.description: This variable states which address format is in use on the Frame Relay interface.

lportDlciAddrLen.name: lportDlciAddrLen
lportDlciAddrLen.description: This variable states which address length in octets. In the case of Q922 format, the length indicates the entire length of the address including the control portion.

lportMaxFramesize.name: lportMaxFramesize
lportMaxFramesize.description: The maximum frame size supported on the interface. Currently it's not used.

lportDceVerifTimer.name: lportDceVerifTimer
lportDceVerifTimer.description: The polling verification timer (secs) on the DCE interface. If the port is configured as a DXI/SNI, then this MIB object defines the heartbeat poll timer setting.

lportDceErrorThresh.name: lportDceErrorThresh
lportDceErrorThresh.description: The error threshold on the DCE interface. If the port is configured as a DXI/SNI, then this MIB object defines the heartbeat poll No Ack threshold setting.

lportDceEventCount.name: lportDceEventCount
lportDceEventCount.description: The monitored events count on the DCE interface.

lportDteErrorThresh.name: lportDteErrorThresh
lportDteErrorThresh.description: The error threshold on the DTE interface.

lportDteEventCount.name: lportDteEventCount
lportDteEventCount.description: The monitored events count on the DTE interface.

lportDtePollTimer.name: lportDtePollTimer
lportDtePollTimer.description: The link status polling timer (secs) on the DTE interface.

lportDteFullCounter.name: lportDteFullCounter
lportDteFullCounter.description: The full status polling counter on the DTE interface.

lportDteMulticast.name: lportDteMulticast
lportDteMulticast.description: The multicast capability of the interface.

lportTrkRnode.name: lportTrkRnode
lportTrkRnode.description: Node at the other end of the trunk. This object is read-write only during lport creation, and read-only thereafter.

lportTrkRlport.name: lportTrkRlport
lportTrkRlport.description: Logical port (IfIndex) at the other end of the trunk. This

lportCongestState.name: lportCongestState
lportCongestState.description: Congestion State for the logical port.

lportQP1Len.name: lportQP1Len
lportQP1Len.description: Priority-1 queue length (number of packets) in xmit buffer.

lportQP2Len.name: lportQP2Len
lportQP2Len.description: Priority-2 queue length (number of packets) in xmit buffer.

lportQP3Len.name: lportQP3Len
lportQP3Len.description: Priority-3 queue length (number of packets) in xmit buffer.

lportQP4Len.name: lportQP4Len
lportQP4Len.description: Priority-4 queue length (number of packets) in xmit buffer.

lportErrTime.name: lportErrTime
lportErrTime.description: The value of sysUpTime at which the last error was detected.

lportErrType.name: lportErrType
lportErrType.description: The type of error that was last seen on this interface.

lportErrData.name: lportErrData
lportErrData.description: An octet string containing as much of the error packet as possible. As a minimum, it must contain the Q.922 Address or as much as was delivered. It is desirable to include all information up to the PDU.

lportDiagTestId.name: lportDiagTestId
lportDiagTestId.description: Identification for the diagnostics tests to be run.

lportDiagTestRuns.name: lportDiagTestRuns
lportDiagTestRuns.description: Number of passes of the diagnostics tests to be run. The default value is 1.

lportDataRate.name: lportDataRate
lportDataRate.description: An estimate of the logical port's data rate in bits per second.

lportTrkStatus.name: lportTrkStatus
lportTrkStatus.description: The current state of the trunk. The btdefined state only applies to backup trunks.

lportSevCongests.name: lportSevCongests
lportSevCongests.description: The cumulative number of times that the lport's congestion state has changed from mildly-congested to severely-congested since the last reset.

lportAbsCongests.name: lportAbsCongests
lportAbsCongests.description: The cumulative number of times that the lport's congestion state has changed from severely-congested to absolutely- congested since the last reset.

lportTrkOverhead.name: lportTrkOverhead
lportTrkOverhead.description: An estimate of the overhead (headers and internal control messages) in trunking user data in terms of a percentage of the configured trunk bandwidth.

lportTrkUtil.name: lportTrkUtil
lportTrkUtil.description: An estimate of the real utilization of the trunk bandwidth in terms of a percentage of the configured trunk bandwidth.

lportTrkLastTimeChange.name: lportTrkLastTimeChange
lportTrkLastTimeChange.description: The sysUpTime value when the trunk was last changed to the current status.

lportCongestRate.name: lportCongestRate
lportCongestRate.description: The rate (%) of entering severely or absolutely congested states in the last one minute interval.

lportCongestRateThresh.name: lportCongestRateThresh
lportCongestRateThresh.description: The alert threshold (%) for the CongestRate; trap will be sent when exceeded.

lportDiagState.name: lportDiagState
lportDiagState.description: The current state of the diagnostic on this logical port.

lportDs0BitStuff.name: lportDs0BitStuff
lportDs0BitStuff.description: Is bit stuffing enabled on this lport?

lportErrorThreshold.name: lportErrorThreshold
lportErrorThreshold.description: The per minute error threshold before a link error trap is sent.

lportUnsyncBandwidth.name: lportUnsyncBandwidth
lportUnsyncBandwidth.description: The accumulated allocated/deallocated bandwidth which has not been propagated by OSPF yet.

lportDTEInStatusFrames.name: lportDTEInStatusFrames
lportDTEInStatusFrames.description: The number of LMI STATUS frames received from the DCE since the last system reset. The count includes link integrity verification frames only.

lportDTEInFullStatusFrames.name: lportDTEInFullStatusFrames
lportDTEInFullStatusFrames.description: The number of LMI Full STATUS frames received from the DTE since the last system reset.

lportDTEInAsyncStatusFrames.name: lportDTEInAsyncStatusFrames
lportDTEInAsyncStatusFrames.description: The number of asynchronous LMI Status frames received from the DTE since the last system reset. For LMI Rev 1, these are Update STATUS frames. For ANSI Annex D and CCITT Annex A these are Asynchronous STATUS frames.

lportDTEInErrorFrames.name: lportDTEInErrorFrames
lportDTEInErrorFrames.description: The number of LMI frames received containing protocol errors.

lportDTEOutPollFrames.name: lportDTEOutPollFrames
lportDTEOutPollFrames.description: The number of LMI Status Enquiry frames transmitted since the last system reset.

lportDTEPollErrorCounts.name: lportDTEPollErrorCounts
lportDTEPollErrorCounts.description: The number of DTE in-channel signaling link reliability errors (i.e. LMI Status Enquiry frames that were not responded to, sequence number errors) since the last system reset.

lportDTEFailCounts.name: lportDTEFailCounts
lportDTEFailCounts.description: The number of times since the last system reset LMI has declared the DTE side of the link down due to excessive errors.

lportDTEFailReason.name: lportDTEFailReason
lportDTEFailReason.description: The LMI failure reason. If the rate of LMI detected errors exceeds the threshold, this contains the cause of the most recent error.

lportDTEOperStatus.name: lportDTEOperStatus
lportDTEOperStatus.description: The operational status of the DTE side of LMI on this link.

lportDCEInPollFrames.name: lportDCEInPollFrames
lportDCEInPollFrames.description: The number of LMI poll frames received from the DTE since the last system reset.

lportDCEInErrorFrames.name: lportDCEInErrorFrames
lportDCEInErrorFrames.description: The number of LMI frames received containing protocol errors.

lportDCEOutStatusFrames.name: lportDCEOutStatusFrames
lportDCEOutStatusFrames.description: The number of LMI STATUS frames transmitted since the last system reset. The count includes link integrity verification frames only.

lportDCEOutFullStatusFrames.name: lportDCEOutFullStatusFrames
lportDCEOutFullStatusFrames.description: The number of LMI Full STATUS frames transmitted since the last system reset.

lportDCEOutAsyncStatusFrames.name: lportDCEOutAsyncStatusFrames
lportDCEOutAsyncStatusFrames.description: The number of asynchronous LMI Status frames transmitted since the last system reset. For LMI Rev 1, these are Update STATUS frames. For ANSI Annex D and CCITT Annex A these are Asynchronous STATUS frames.

lportDCEPollErrorCounts.name: lportDCEPollErrorCounts
lportDCEPollErrorCounts.description: The number of DCE in-channel signaling link reliability errors (i.e. timeouts waiting for LMI Status Enquiry frames, sequence number errors) since the last system reset.

lportDCEFailCounts.name: lportDCEFailCounts
lportDCEFailCounts.description: The number of times since the last system reset LMI has declared the DCE side of the link down due to excessive errors.

lportDCEFailReason.name: lportDCEFailReason
lportDCEFailReason.description: The LMI failure reason. If the rate of LMI detected errors exceeds the threshold, this contains the cause of the most recent error.

lportDCEOperStatus.name: lportDCEOperStatus
lportDCEOperStatus.description: The operational status of the DCE side of LMI on this link.

lportDCEOperDlcmiStd.name: lportDCEOperDlcmiStd
lportDCEOperDlcmiStd.description: This variable states which Data Link Connection Management scheme is actually being run on this link. This is used for DCE links configured for AutoDetect and indicates the LMI standard used in the last poll received from the DTE.

lportLMIInErrorFrames.name: lportLMIInErrorFrames
lportLMIInErrorFrames.description: The number of total frames received with an error. For NNI links this is the sum of lportDTEInErrorFrames and lportDCEInErrorFrames.

lportDCEnN4.name: lportDCEnN4
lportDCEnN4.description: This variable specifies the maximum number of LMI Status Enquiry frames that can be received from a DTE within time interval lportDCEnT3. This is only valid on lports using LMIREV1.

lportDCEnT3.name: lportDCEnT3
lportDCEnT3.description: This variable specifies the time interval (secs) used to determine if lportDCEnN4 an excess number (lportDCEnN4) of Status Enquiry messages are received. This is only valid on lports using LMIREV1.

lportXmitLatencyThreshold.name: lportXmitLatencyThreshold
lportXmitLatencyThreshold.description: Outbound frames are allowed on the transmit commit queue when the commit queue falls below this threshold (in microseconds).

lportXmitRefillPriority0Percentage.name: lportXmitRefillPriority0Percentage
lportXmitRefillPriority0Percentage.description: Percentage of time the transmit queue is refilled in priority order 0, 1, 2, 3.

lportXmitRefillPriority1Percentage.name: lportXmitRefillPriority1Percentage
lportXmitRefillPriority1Percentage.description: Percentage of time the transmit queue is refilled in priority order 1, 2, 3, 0.

lportXmitRefillPriority2Percentage.name: lportXmitRefillPriority2Percentage
lportXmitRefillPriority2Percentage.description: Percentage of time the transmit queue is refilled in priority order 2, 3, 0, 1.

lportXmitRefillPriority3Percentage.name: lportXmitRefillPriority3Percentage
lportXmitRefillPriority3Percentage.description: Percentage of time the transmit queue is refilled in priority order 3, 0, 1, 2.

lportXmitDiscardLow.name: lportXmitDiscardLow
lportXmitDiscardLow.description: Priority holding queue low water discard threshold. Discarding stops when holding queue hits this level.

lportSevereThreshold.name: lportSevereThreshold
lportSevereThreshold.description: Severe congestion level. Outbound red and amber packets are discarded when the transmit queue hits this threshold.

lportMildThreshold.name: lportMildThreshold
lportMildThreshold.description: Mild congestion level. Outbound red packets are discarded when the transmit queue hits this threshold.

lportTrkKeepAliveTimer.name: lportTrkKeepAliveTimer
lportTrkKeepAliveTimer.description: Send a keep-alive packet after this many seconds. These packets are sent on trunk links only. The range is 0 thru 15, with zero meaning the keep-alive protocol is disabled. The default is one.

lportTrkKeepAliveErrorThreshold.name: lportTrkKeepAliveErrorThreshold
lportTrkKeepAliveErrorThreshold.description: Declare the interface down after this many keep-alive packets in a row are missed. The default is five.

lportIgCutThruStatus.name: lportIgCutThruStatus
lportIgCutThruStatus.description: Enable ingress cut-thru on this user lport. Default is disabled.

lportEgCutThruStatus.name: lportEgCutThruStatus
lportEgCutThruStatus.description: Enable egress cut-thru on this user lport. Default is disabled.

lportEgCutThruThresh.name: lportEgCutThruThresh
lportEgCutThruThresh.description: Egress cut thru threshold - start transmitting a frame on a user port after this many segments have arrived.

lportFrameRelayTrkEnable.name: lportFrameRelayTrkEnable
lportFrameRelayTrkEnable.description: Allow Frame Relay Trunks on the user link.

lportSmdsSsiIf.name: lportSmdsSsiIf
lportSmdsSsiIf.description: The interface number of the SSI which this DXI/SNI is multiplexed to.

lportSmdsSsiSlot.name: lportSmdsSsiSlot
lportSmdsSsiSlot.description: The slot of the SSI which this DXI/SNI is multiplexed to.

lportSmdsScrnId.name: lportSmdsScrnId
lportSmdsScrnId.description: The ID of address screen for this interface.

lportSmdsIaScrnMap.name: lportSmdsIaScrnMap
lportSmdsIaScrnMap.description: The individual address screen member bit map. For set request, the first byte is the operation : 1 for deleting, 2 for adding. The following bytes are the bit map. The bit position of each bit in this bit map represent a screen member ID. The most significant bit is corresponding to group address ID 1. For get response, The whole string is the bit map.

lportSmdsGaScrnMap.name: lportSmdsGaScrnMap
lportSmdsGaScrnMap.description: The group address screen member bit map. For set request, the first byte is the operation : 1 for deleting, 2 for adding. The following bytes are the bit map. The bit position of each bit in this bit map represent a screen member ID. The most significant bit is corresponding to group address ID 1. For get response, The whole string is the bit map.

lportSmdsTrkAddr.name: lportSmdsTrkAddr
lportSmdsTrkAddr.description: SMDS address. For SSI feeder port, this address is the local address of all SMDS optimim paths associated with this SSI feeder port. For SSI Optimum path port, this address is the remote address of this SSI optimum path. The 4 most significant bits are 1100. The following 4 bits are 0001. The following 5 bytes are the 10 digits number in BCD format. The following 16 bits are padded with 1's

lportSmdsCpePoll.name: lportSmdsCpePoll
lportSmdsCpePoll.description: Whether CPE supports heart beat poll or not.

lportSmdsPduCheck.name: lportSmdsPduCheck
lportSmdsPduCheck.description: turn of/off the detailed SIP3 PDU error checking.

lportSmdsCntOutFrDxi2HbPolls.name: lportSmdsCntOutFrDxi2HbPolls
lportSmdsCntOutFrDxi2HbPolls.description: Number of DXI2 heart beat poll frames transmitted.

lportSmdsCntOutByteDxi2HbPolls.name: lportSmdsCntOutByteDxi2HbPolls
lportSmdsCntOutByteDxi2HbPolls.description: Total number of octets in DXI2 heart beat poll frames transmitted.

lportSmdsCntInFrDxi2HbPolls.name: lportSmdsCntInFrDxi2HbPolls
lportSmdsCntInFrDxi2HbPolls.description: Number of DXI2 heart beat poll frames received.

lportSmdsCntInByteDxi2HbPolls.name: lportSmdsCntInByteDxi2HbPolls
lportSmdsCntInByteDxi2HbPolls.description: Total number of octets in DXI2 heart beat poll frames received.

lportSmdsCntOutByteSip3s.name: lportSmdsCntOutByteSip3s
lportSmdsCntOutByteSip3s.description: Total number of octets in SIP3 frames transmitted.

lportSmdsCntInByteSip3s.name: lportSmdsCntInByteSip3s
lportSmdsCntInByteSip3s.description: Total number of octets in SIP3 frames received.

lportSmdsCntDxi2LinkIdInvalids.name: lportSmdsCntDxi2LinkIdInvalids
lportSmdsCntDxi2LinkIdInvalids.description: Number of instances that DXI2 link ID is invalid.

lportSmdsCntDxi2StationIdInvalids.name: lportSmdsCntDxi2StationIdInvalids
lportSmdsCntDxi2StationIdInvalids.description: Number of instances that DXI2 station ID is invalid.

lportSmdsCntDxi2CrInvalids.name: lportSmdsCntDxi2CrInvalids
lportSmdsCntDxi2CrInvalids.description: Number of instances that DXI2 command/response field is invalid.

lportSmdsCntDxi2AeInvalids.name: lportSmdsCntDxi2AeInvalids
lportSmdsCntDxi2AeInvalids.description: Number of instances that DXI2 address extension field is invalid.

lportSmdsCntDxi2CtrlInvalids.name: lportSmdsCntDxi2CtrlInvalids
lportSmdsCntDxi2CtrlInvalids.description: Number of instances that DXI2 control field is invalid.

lportSmdsCntDxi2FrameSizeErrors.name: lportSmdsCntDxi2FrameSizeErrors
lportSmdsCntDxi2FrameSizeErrors.description: Number of instances there is a DXI2 frame size error.

lportSmdsCntSip3RsvdInvalids.name: lportSmdsCntSip3RsvdInvalids
lportSmdsCntSip3RsvdInvalids.description: Number of instances that SIP3 reserved field in header is invalid.

lportSmdsCntSip3BetagMismatchs.name: lportSmdsCntSip3BetagMismatchs
lportSmdsCntSip3BetagMismatchs.description: Number of instances that SIP3 BE tag is not macthed.

lportSmdsCntSip3BasizeIncorrects.name: lportSmdsCntSip3BasizeIncorrects
lportSmdsCntSip3BasizeIncorrects.description: Number of instances that SIP3 BA size is incorrect.

lportSmdsCntSip3BasizeInvalids.name: lportSmdsCntSip3BasizeInvalids
lportSmdsCntSip3BasizeInvalids.description: Number of instances that SIP3 BA size is invalid.

lportSmdsCntSip3DaTypeInvalids.name: lportSmdsCntSip3DaTypeInvalids
lportSmdsCntSip3DaTypeInvalids.description: Number of instances that SIP3 destination address type is invalid.

lportSmdsCntSip3DaInvalids.name: lportSmdsCntSip3DaInvalids
lportSmdsCntSip3DaInvalids.description: Number of instances that SIP3 destination address is invalid.

lportSmdsCntSip3SaTypeInvalids.name: lportSmdsCntSip3SaTypeInvalids
lportSmdsCntSip3SaTypeInvalids.description: Number of instances that SIP3 source address type is invalid.

lportSmdsCntSip3SaInvalids.name: lportSmdsCntSip3SaInvalids
lportSmdsCntSip3SaInvalids.description: Number of instances that SIP3 source address is invalid.

lportSmdsCntSip3BasizeMismatchs.name: lportSmdsCntSip3BasizeMismatchs
lportSmdsCntSip3BasizeMismatchs.description: Number of instances that SIP3 BA sizes in the header and trailer are not matched.

lportSmdsCntSip3HeLenInvalids.name: lportSmdsCntSip3HeLenInvalids
lportSmdsCntSip3HeLenInvalids.description: Number of instances that SIP3 header extension length is invalid.

cktMcastParentGroups.name: cktMcastParentGroups
