cktDiagTestRuns.name: cktDiagTestRuns
cktDiagTestRuns.description: Number of passes of the diagnostics tests to be run. The default value is 1.

cktHelloCounter.name: cktHelloCounter
cktHelloCounter.description: Number of PVC hello pdu frames received in the VC entry of the called side.

cktHelloAckCounter.name: cktHelloAckCounter
cktHelloAckCounter.description: Number of PVC hello Ack pdu frames received in the VC entry of the calling side.

cktDefinedPath.name: cktDefinedPath
cktDefinedPath.description: User defined path. in the format of Nx,x,x,Nx,.... If x is not prefixed with 'N', x is an interface ID. If x is prefixed with `N`, x is a node ID.

cktDefinedPathEnable.name: cktDefinedPathEnable
cktDefinedPathEnable.description: If set to 1, it means there is an user defined path for this circuit and it is enabled.

cktDefinedPathAltOption.name: cktDefinedPathAltOption
cktDefinedPathAltOption.description: If set to 1, it means that if the user defined path fails, use the ospf-determined path.

cktUsingDefinedPath.name: cktUsingDefinedPath
cktUsingDefinedPath.description: If set to 1, it indicates the PVC is currently using the defined path.

cktTryAltPath.name: cktTryAltPath
cktTryAltPath.description: If set to 1, it means the inactive PVC will be activated on the ospf-determined path in the next retry.

cktNotVirgin.name: cktNotVirgin
cktNotVirgin.description: If set to 1, it means this VC entry has been successfuly activated before.

cktInForward.name: cktInForward
cktInForward.description: If the value is 1, it means the inbound flow is OK.

cktBtusSeg.name: cktBtusSeg
cktBtusSeg.description: Number of Bus xmit units per data segment

cktInSegmentsDiscards.name: cktInSegmentsDiscards
cktInSegmentsDiscards.description: Number of segments received that were discarded because of frame reassembly errors.

cktAtmVPI.name: cktAtmVPI
cktAtmVPI.description: VPI value in the ATM cell header: ATM DXI with HSSI IOP VPI (4 lsb bit) range: 0 - 15 ATM UNI DS3/E3 IOP VPI (4 lsb bit) range: 0 - 15 T1 ATM 4 lsb range 0-15 ATM-IWU STM-1/STS-3c VPI (<=12 lsb bit) range: 0-4095

cktAtmVCI.name: cktAtmVCI
cktAtmVCI.description: VCI value in the ATM cell header: ATM DXI with HSSI IOP VCI (6 lsb bit) range: 0 - 63 ATM UNI DS3/E3 IOP VCI (8 lsb bit) range: 0 - 255 T1 ATM 4 lsb VCI (6 lsb bit) range 0 - 255 ATM-IWU STM-1/STS-3c VCI (<=12 lsb bit) range: 0-4095

cktType.name: cktType
cktType.description: 1 if a permanent virtual circuit; 2 if a switched virtual circuit.

cktSvcCallingParty.name: cktSvcCallingParty
cktSvcCallingParty.description: The calling party number if this is a switched virtual circuit.

cktSvcCalledParty.name: cktSvcCalledParty
cktSvcCalledParty.description: The called party number if this is a switched virtual circuit.

cktSvcDuration.name: cktSvcDuration
cktSvcDuration.description: The duration since the SVC circuit has been running.

cktSvcCause.name: cktSvcCause
cktSvcCause.description: SVC cause number. The index will be 0.0 and should be disregarded. The following cause numbers maybe returned by stdx: 1 - unassigned number, callee is not assigned 2 - no route to specified transit network 3 - no route to destination 6 - channel unacceptable 16 - normal clearing 17 - user busy 18 - no user responding 21 - call rejected by whoever is sending this cause 22 - number changed, called party has changed its number 27 - destination out of order (the interface to called user) 28 - called party number is invalid 29 - facility requested can't be provided by network 30 - included in STATUS message to indicate it is responding to a STATUS ENQUIRY 31 - unspecified, used if no other cause is appropriate 34 - no circuit or channel available to handle the call 38 - network is out of order 41 - tempprary failure, i.e., caller may try again 42 - network congestion 43 - access information (user-to-user) discarded 44 - requested circuit unavailable 58 - bearer capability not available 63 - requested service unavailable 65 - requested bearer capability is not implemented 81 - call reference is unknown 95 - invalid message 96 - mandatory information element is missing 97 - message type is unknown 98 - message not compatible with call state 99 - information element is unknown or not implemented 100 - invalid information element contents 101 - message not compatible with call state

cktXlatFlag.name: cktXlatFlag
cktXlatFlag.description: 0 if RFC1490 or no translation; 1 if RFC1483 translation.

cktDestLaddr.name: cktDestLaddr
cktDestLaddr.description: The destination logical address of the circuit.

cktSrcLaddr.name: cktSrcLaddr
cktSrcLaddr.description: The source logical address of the circuit.

cktLoop.name: cktLoop
cktLoop.description: Setting this variable controls the loopback status of the given circuit endpoint.

cktRerouteBalance.name: cktRerouteBalance
cktRerouteBalance.description: Setting this variable controls the use of rerouting to balance link usage.

cktCallingBackup.name: cktCallingBackup
cktCallingBackup.description: Indicates if a caller endpoint is calling a backup PVC.

cktRCir.name: cktRCir
cktRCir.description: The average number of user data (bits) that the network agrees to transfer over the circuit in the opposite direction, measured over the measurement interval T = cktBc/cktCir.

cktAtmQoS.name: cktAtmQoS
cktAtmQoS.description: The Quality of Service of the ATM Circuit. Valid only for ATM type circuits.

cktAtmInCells.name: cktAtmInCells
cktAtmInCells.description: The Number of ATM cells received on a VC (VPC or VCC).

cktAtmOutCells.name: cktAtmOutCells
cktAtmOutCells.description: The Number of ATM cells transmitted on a VC (VPC or VCC)..

cktAtmInDiscardedClp0Cells.name: cktAtmInDiscardedClp0Cells
cktAtmInDiscardedClp0Cells.description: The Number of ATM CLP0 cells received and discarded on a VC (VPC or VCC)..

cktAtmInDiscardedClp1Cells.name: cktAtmInDiscardedClp1Cells
cktAtmInDiscardedClp1Cells.description: The Number of ATM CLP1 cells received and discarded on a VC (VPC or VCC).

cktAtmVcType.name: cktAtmVcType
cktAtmVcType.description: Type of ATM connection (VPC or VCC).

cktAtmPCR.name: cktAtmPCR
cktAtmPCR.description: The Peak Cell Rate measured in cells/second at which cells are transmitted for this circuit.

cktAtmSCR.name: cktAtmSCR
cktAtmSCR.description: The Sustainable Cell Rate is the average transmission rate in cells per second for this circuit. It must be less than or or equal to the Peak Cell Rate.

cktAtmMBS.name: cktAtmMBS
cktAtmMBS.description: The Maximum Burst size determines the maximum number of cells that can be transmitted at the peak cell rate.

cktAtmInPassedClp0Cells.name: cktAtmInPassedClp0Cells
cktAtmInPassedClp0Cells.description: The Number of ATM CLP 0 cells received and passed UPC on a VC (VPC or VCC).

cktAtmInPassedClp1Cells.name: cktAtmInPassedClp1Cells
cktAtmInPassedClp1Cells.description: The Number of ATM CLP 1 cells received and passed UPC on a VC (VPC or VCC).

cktAtmInTaggedCells.name: cktAtmInTaggedCells
cktAtmInTaggedCells.description: The Number of ATM cells received and tagged on a VC (VPC or VCC).

cktAtmOutClp0Cells.name: cktAtmOutClp0Cells
cktAtmOutClp0Cells.description: The Number of ATM CLP 0 cells transmitted on a VC (VPC or VCC)..

cktAtmOutClp1Cells.name: cktAtmOutClp1Cells
cktAtmOutClp1Cells.description: The Number of ATM CLP 1 cells transmitted on a VC (VPC or VCC)..

cktAtmRQoS.name: cktAtmRQoS
cktAtmRQoS.description: The Quality of Service of the ATM connection in the opposite direction.

cktAtmRTfdType.name: cktAtmRTfdType
cktAtmRTfdType.description: The combination of traffic parameters in opposite direction.

cktAtmRTfdParam1.name: cktAtmRTfdParam1
cktAtmRTfdParam1.description: The traffic descriptor parameter 1 for opposite direction.

cktAtmRTfdParam2.name: cktAtmRTfdParam2
cktAtmRTfdParam2.description: The traffic descriptor parameter 3 for opposite direction.

cktAtmRTfdParam3.name: cktAtmRTfdParam3
cktAtmRTfdParam3.description: The traffic descriptor parameter 3 for opposite direction.

cktRBc.name: cktRBc
cktRBc.description: The maximum amount of data (bits) that the network agrees to transfer over the circuit in the opposite direction under normal conditions, during the measurement interval.

cktRBe.name: cktRBe
cktRBe.description: The maximum amount of uncommitted data (bits) that the network will attempt to transfer over the circuit in the opposite direction during the measurement interval. By default, if not configured when creating the entry, the Excess Information Burst Size is set to the value of ifSpeed.

cktOamLoopbackDirection.name: cktOamLoopbackDirection
cktOamLoopbackDirection.description: Which direction to send the loopback cell. If 'local', send out this circuit entry's port. If 'remote', send out the remote circuit entry's port.

cktOamLoopbackType.name: cktOamLoopbackType
cktOamLoopbackType.description: Type of oam loopback to send - either segment or end to end.

cktOamLoopbackHops.name: cktOamLoopbackHops
cktOamLoopbackHops.description: Number of hops the loopback cell should traverse inside the Cascade network before being echoed back by the far Cascade device.

cktOamLoopbackCount.name: cktOamLoopbackCount
cktOamLoopbackCount.description: Number of oam loopback cells left to send this session. Setting this from zero to non-zero starts the loopback session.

cktOamLoopbackReceived.name: cktOamLoopbackReceived
cktOamLoopbackReceived.description: Number of oam responses received for this loopback session.

cktOamLoopbackTimeouts.name: cktOamLoopbackTimeouts
cktOamLoopbackTimeouts.description: Number of times a loopback response was not received within the timeout period during this loopback session.

cktOamLoopbackReceivedHigh.name: cktOamLoopbackReceivedHigh
cktOamLoopbackReceivedHigh.description: Highest response time (in milliseconds) of an oam loopback response this loopback session.

cktOamLoopbackReceivedLow.name: cktOamLoopbackReceivedLow
cktOamLoopbackReceivedLow.description: Lowest response time (in milliseconds) of an oam loopback response this loopback session.

cktOamLoopbackReceivedAvg.name: cktOamLoopbackReceivedAvg
cktOamLoopbackReceivedAvg.description: Average response time (in milliseconds) of an oam loopback response this loopback session.

cktOamAlarmDisable.name: cktOamAlarmDisable
cktOamAlarmDisable.description: If disabled, then don't generate oam alarms if this circuit is down.

cktShaperId.name: cktShaperId
cktShaperId.description: The shaper to be used for this virtual connection interworking with frame relay: 1-port ATM-IWU STM-1/STS-3c card -------------------------------- Values: 1..16

cktOspfCtd.name: cktOspfCtd
cktOspfCtd.description: The allowed cell delay: 4-port CBR E1/DS1 card ---------------------- The maximum allowed cell delay in msec

cktOspfCdv.name: cktOspfCdv
cktOspfCdv.description: The allowed cell delay variation: 4-port CBR E1/DS1 card ---------------------- The maximum allowed cell delay variation in msec

cktOutPort.name: cktOutPort
cktOutPort.description: The outgoing port number for the adjacent VC entry in this switch.

cktOutVc.name: cktOutVc
cktOutVc.description: The adjacent VC entry corresponding to this circuit accross the bus.

cktRVc.name: cktRVc
cktRVc.description: The adjacent VC entry corresponding to this circuit accross the trunk.

cktEntryType.name: cktEntryType
cktEntryType.description: The internal type of circuit entry allocated by the circuit manager.

cktSvcAalType.name: cktSvcAalType
cktSvcAalType.description: The AAL type for this SVC.

cktSvcBBearerClass.name: cktSvcBBearerClass
cktSvcBBearerClass.description: The Broadband bearer capability class for this SVC.

cktSvcBBearerClippingSusc.name: cktSvcBBearerClippingSusc
cktSvcBBearerClippingSusc.description: The Broadband bearer capability clipping susceptibility for this SVC.

cktSvcBBearerTmgReq.name: cktSvcBBearerTmgReq
cktSvcBBearerTmgReq.description: The Broadband bearer capability timing requirements for this SVC.

cktSvcBBearerTfcType.name: cktSvcBBearerTfcType
cktSvcBBearerTfcType.description: The Broadband bearer capability traffic type for this SVC.

cktRPriority.name: cktRPriority
cktRPriority.description: The priority level (0 through 3) for this circuit in the opposite direction. When port service type is defined as 'mono-class', this priority means the forward priority of the circuit. When port service type is defined as 'multi-class', this priority means the discard priority of the circuit.

cktRtPriority.name: cktRtPriority
cktRtPriority.description: The routing priority level of the circuit which is a 8 bit number where the 3-bit bumping priority is contained in bits 0-2 and the 4-bit bandwidth priority is contained in bits 3-6. For ATM multipoint ckts, bw and bumping priorities should be zero.

cktDeltaBc.name: cktDeltaBc
cktDeltaBc.description: The maximum number of bits that the network agree to transfer over the circuit as committed bits during the measurement interval under the CONDITION that the circuit still has POSITIVE committed bit (Bc) credits before receiving a frame but will have NEGATIVE Bc credits after accepting the frame. The range of this variable is 0 to 65,528 bits. By default, if not configured when creating the entry, it is set to 65,528 bits.

cktDeltaBe.name: cktDeltaBe
cktDeltaBe.description: The maximum number of bits that the network agree to transfer over the circuit as allowed excess bits during the measurement interval under the CONDITION that the circuit still has POSITIVE excess bit (Be) credits before receiving a frame but will have NEGATIVE Be credits after accepting the frame. The range of this variable is 0 to 65,528 bits. By default, if not configured when creating the entry, it is set to 65,528 bits.

cktDeltaRBc.name: cktDeltaRBc
cktDeltaRBc.description: The maximum number of bits that the network agree to transfer over the circuit as committed bits in the opposite direction during the measurement interval under the CONDITION that the circuit still has POSITIVE committed bit (Bc) credits before receiving a frame but will have NEGATIVE Bc credits after accepting the frame. The range of this variable is 0 to 65,528 bits. By default, if not configured when creating the entry, it is set to 65,528 bits.

cktDeltaRBe.name: cktDeltaRBe
cktDeltaRBe.description: The maximum number of bits that the network agree to transfer over the circuit as allowed excess bits in the opposite direction during the measurement interval under the CONDITION that the circuit still has POSITIVE excess bit (Be) credits before receiving a frame but will have NEGATIVE Be credits after accepting the frame. The range of this variable is 0 to 65,528 bits. By default, if not configured when creating the entry, it is set to 65,528 bits.

cktRedFrPcnt.name: cktRedFrPcnt
cktRedFrPcnt.description: The percentage of RED frame bits that are allowed to enter the network, during the measurement interval, under non-congestion condition. Its value range is 0 - 100 and default value is 100. Its calculation is as follows: cktRedFrPcn = (allowed RED frame bits)/(Bc+Be+allowed RED frame bits)

cktRedFrRPcnt.name: cktRedFrRPcnt
cktRedFrRPcnt.description: The percentage of RED frame bits that are allowed to enter the network in the opposite direction, during the measurement interval, under non-congestion condition. Its value range is 0 - 100 and default value is 100. Its calculation is as follows: cktRedFrRPcn = (allowed RED frame bits)/(rBc+rBe+allowed RED frame bits)

cktRateEnforceSchm.name: cktRateEnforceSchm
cktRateEnforceSchm.description: Variable used to indicate the rate enforcement scheme employed. 0: Slide window rate enforcement scheme 1: Jump window rate enforcement scheme 2: Simple rate enforcement scheme Default value is 2.

cktRateEnforceRSchm.name: cktRateEnforceRSchm
cktRateEnforceRSchm.description: Variable used to indicate the rate enforcement scheme employed in the opposite direction. 0: Slide window rate enforcement scheme 1: Jump window rate enforcement scheme 2: Simple rate enforcement scheme Default value is 2.

cktROde.name: cktROde
cktROde.description: This variable states whether graceful discard is enabled for the ckt in the opposite direction.

cktPrivateNet.name: cktPrivateNet
cktPrivateNet.description: If non-zero, indicates the private network that the circuit belongs to. If 0, the circuit has access to the entire public portion of the network.

cktPrivateNetOverflow.name: cktPrivateNetOverflow
cktPrivateNetOverflow.description: Indicates how private network circuits are handled, when the resources of the network have become exhausted. If set to use-public, the resources of the public network can be used during overflow conditions.

cktCustomerID.name: cktCustomerID
cktCustomerID.description: The Customer that owns this circuit. For Virtual Private Networking Support.

cktAtmCDVT.name: cktAtmCDVT
cktAtmCDVT.description: The Cell Delay Variation Tolerance for the VC

cktNdcEnable.name: cktNdcEnable
cktNdcEnable.description: Enable/disable Network Data Collection for a PVC on an IOM. The number of NDC-monitored PVCs is limited as follows: 30 per DS3 interface, 90 per OC3 interface, and 360 per OC12 interface.

cktInterworkingFrToAtmCLP.name: cktInterworkingFrToAtmCLP
cktInterworkingFrToAtmCLP.description: CLP mapping for Frame Relay To ATM Service Interworking.

cktInterworkingFrToAtmDe.name: cktInterworkingFrToAtmDe
cktInterworkingFrToAtmDe.description: DE bit mapping for ATM To Frame Relay Service Interworking.

cktNrtsCLP1.name: cktNrtsCLP1
cktNrtsCLP1.description: Whether to use the discard threshold as the CLP1 Discard threshold upon reception of a cell by the NRTS processor in the forward direction.

cktNrtsDiscardClp0.name: cktNrtsDiscardClp0
cktNrtsDiscardClp0.description: The number of the CLP0 cells received and discarded by the NRTS processor.

cktNrtsDiscardClp1.name: cktNrtsDiscardClp1
cktNrtsDiscardClp1.description: The number of the CLP1 cells received and discarded by the NRTS processor.

cktMPEnableAMF.name: cktMPEnableAMF
cktMPEnableAMF.description: Whether the Multilink PPP PVC Attributes Modification Feature is enabled.

cktMPEligible.name: cktMPEligible
cktMPEligible.description: Whether this circuit is eligible to be a member of a Multilink PPP bundle.

cktMPForcedCaller.name: cktMPForcedCaller
cktMPForcedCaller.description: Whether this end of the circuit has been forced to be caller to support Multilink PPP PVC Attributes Modification Feature.

cktMPForcedCallee.name: cktMPForcedCallee
cktMPForcedCallee.description: Whether this end of the circuit has been forced to be callee to support Multilink PPP PVC Attributes Modification Feature.

cktFrameSize.name: cktFrameSize
cktFrameSize.description: The average frame size (measured in number of bytes) of the traffic on the circuit. If not configured, it is set to 280 (bytes) by default.

cktRFrameSize.name: cktRFrameSize
cktRFrameSize.description: The average frame size (measured in number of bytes) of the traffic on the circuit on the reverse direction. If not configured, it is set to 280 (bytes) by default.

cktRNrtsCLP1.name: cktRNrtsCLP1
cktRNrtsCLP1.description: Whether to use the discard threshold as the CLP1 Discard threshold upon reception of a cell by the NRTS processor in the reverse direction.

cktBBearerAtmTransferCapability.name: cktBBearerAtmTransferCapability
cktBBearerAtmTransferCapability.description: The broadband bearer ATM transfer capability of this SVC. This object is not pertinent to IISP 3.x, UNI 3.x or Q.2931 signaling.

cktAtmFrameDiscard.name: cktAtmFrameDiscard
cktAtmFrameDiscard.description: The ATM frame discard state for this circuit.

cktRAtmFrameDiscard.name: cktRAtmFrameDiscard
cktRAtmFrameDiscard.description: The reverse ATM frame discard state for this circuit.

cktAbrFRMRTT.name: cktAbrFRMRTT
cktAbrFRMRTT.description: The ABR fixed RM round trip time for this SVC.

cktAbrICR.name: cktAbrICR
cktAbrICR.description: The ABR initial cell rate for this SVC.

cktRAbrICR.name: cktRAbrICR
cktRAbrICR.description: The reverse ABR initial cell rate for this SVC.

cktAbrRIF.name: cktAbrRIF
cktAbrRIF.description: The ABR rate increase factor for this SVC.

cktRAbrRIF.name: cktRAbrRIF
cktRAbrRIF.description: The reverse ABR rate increase factor for this SVC.

cktAbrRDF.name: cktAbrRDF
cktAbrRDF.description: The ABR rate decrease factor for this SVC.

cktRAbrRDF.name: cktRAbrRDF

dsx1LineType.name: dsx1LineType
dsx1LineType.description: This variable indicates the variety of DS1 Line implementing this circuit. The type of circuit affects the number of bits per second that the circuit can reasonably carry, as well as the interpretation of the usage and error statistics. The values, in sequence, describe: TITLE: SPECIFICATION: dsx1ESF Extended SuperFrame DS1 dsx1D4 AT&T D4 format DS1 dsx1E1 CCITT Recommendation G.704 (Table 4a) dsx1E1-CRC CCITT Recommendation G.704 (Table 4b) dsxE1-MF G.704 (Table 4a) with TS16 multiframing enabled dsx1E1-CRC-MF G.704 (Table 4b) with TS16 multiframing enabled

dsx1LineCoding.name: dsx1LineCoding
dsx1LineCoding.description: This variable describes the variety of Zero Code Suppression used on the link, which in turn affects a number of its characteristics. dsx1JBZS refers the Jammed Bit Zero Suppres- sion, in which the AT&T specification of at least one pulse every 8 bit periods is literal- ly implemented by forcing a pulse in bit 8 of each channel. Thus, only seven bits per chan- nel, or 1.344 Mbps, is available for data. dsx1B8ZS refers to the use of a specified pat- tern of normal bits and bipolar violations which are used to replace a sequence of eight zero bits. ANSI Clear Channels may use dsx1ZBTSI, or Zero Byte Time Slot Interchange. E1 links, with or without CRC, use dsx1HDB3 or dsx1AMI. dsx1AMI refers to a mode wherein no zero code suppression is present and the line encoding does not solve the problem directly. In this application, the higher layer must provide data which meets or exceeds the pulse density re- quirements, such as inverting HDLC data.

dsx1SendCode.name: dsx1SendCode
dsx1SendCode.description: This variable indicates what type of code is being sent across the DS1 interface by the dev- ice. The values mean: dsx1SendNoCode sending looped or normal data dsx1SendLineCode sending a request for a line loopback dsx1SendPayloadCode sending a request for a payload loopback dsx1SendResetCode sending a loopback termination request dsx1SendQRS sending a Quasi-Random Signal (QRS) test pattern dsx1Send511Pattern sending a 511 bit fixed test pattern dsx1Send3in24Pattern sending a fixed test pattern of 3 bits set in 24 dsx1SendOtherTestPattern sending a test pattern other than those described by this object

dsx1CircuitIdentifier.name: dsx1CircuitIdentifier
dsx1CircuitIdentifier.description: This variable contains the transmission vendor's circuit identifier, for the purpose of facilitating troubleshooting.

dsx1LoopbackConfig.name: dsx1LoopbackConfig
dsx1LoopbackConfig.description: This variable represents the loopback confi- guration of the DS1 interface. Agents support- ing read/write access should return badValue in response to a requested loopback state that the interface does not support. The values mean: dsx1NoLoop Not in the loopback state. A device that is not capable of performing a loopback on the interface shall always return this as it's value. dsx1PayloadLoop The received signal at this interface is looped through the device. Typically the received signal is looped back for re- transmission after it has passed through the device's framing function. dsx1LineLoop The received signal at this interface does not go through the device (minimum pene- tration) but is looped back out. dsx1OtherLoop Loopbacks that are not defined here.

dsx1LineStatus.name: dsx1LineStatus
dsx1LineStatus.description: This variable indicates the Line Status of the interface. It contains loopback, failure, re- ceived 'alarm' and transmitted 'alarm' infor- mation. The dsx1LineStatus is a bit map represented as a sum, therefore, it can represent multiple failures (alarms) and a LoopbackState simultaneously. dsx1NoAlarm should be set if and only if no other flag is set. If the dsx1LoopbackState bit is set, the loopback in ef- fect can be determined from the dsx1LoopbackConfig object. The various bit positions are: 1 dsx1NoAlarm No Alarm Present 2 dsx1RcvFarEndLOF Far end LOF (a.k.a., Yellow Alarm) 4 dsx1XmtFarEndLOF Near end sending LOF Indication 8 dsx1RcvAIS Far end sending AIS 16 dsx1XmtAIS Near end sending AIS 32 dsx1LossOfFrame Near end LOF (a.k.a., Red Alarm) 64 dsx1LossOfSignal Near end Loss Of Signal 128 dsx1LoopbackState Near end is looped 256 dsx1T16AIS E1 TS16 AIS 512 dsx1RcvFarEndLOMF Far End Sending TS16 LOMF 1024 dsx1XmtFarEndLOMF Near End Sending TS16 LOMF 2048 dsx1RcvTestCode Near End detects a test code 4096 dsx1OtherFailure any line status not defined here

'bitOriented' indicates that E1 Channel Asso- ciated Signaling is in use. 'messageOriented' indicates that Common Chan- nel Signaling is in use either on channel 16 of an E1 link or channel 24 of a T1.

dsx1TransmitClockSource.name: dsx1TransmitClockSource

'localTiming' indicates that a local clock source is used. 'throughTiming' indicates that recovered re- ceive clock from another interface is used as the transmit clock.

E.164 addresses are coded as 1-15 ASCII octets Atm-endsystem addresses are coded as 20 octet binary addresses.

svcConfigCgPtyInsertionMode.name: svcConfigCgPtyInsertionMode
svcConfigCgPtyInsertionMode.description: This object determines whether a statically configured address shall be inserted in the calling party address IE for calls entering the network at this port.

svcConfigCgPtyInsertionAddress.name: svcConfigCgPtyInsertionAddress

svcConfigCgPtyScreenMode.name: svcConfigCgPtyScreenMode
svcConfigCgPtyScreenMode.description: The type of screening to perform on the calling party number for calls entering the network at this port. Screening will be conducted by performing a bit-wise (for prefixes) or byte-wise (for addresses) comparison of the calling party number with the appropriate prefix or address database(s), as configured.

svcConfigEgressAddrXlateMode.name: svcConfigEgressAddrXlateMode
svcConfigEgressAddrXlateMode.description: This object determines the type of address translation, if any to occur for calls exiting the network at this port. The tunnelling mode will screen the called address against the prefixes configured for this port. If no match is found, no action is taken. If a remote gateway address is configured for the matching prefix entry, the called party address will be tunnelled as a called subaddress and the configured remote gateway address will be inserted as the called party address. If a local gateway address is configured for the matching prefix entry, the calling party address, if present, will be tunnelled as a calling subaddress and the configured local gateway address, if present, will be inserted as the calling party. The replacement mode will operate as does the tunnelling mode, except the original called and calling party addresses will be discarded. The two translation modes are used for address interworking between networks using E.164 ATM Endsystem addresses and native ISDN E.164 addresses.

svcConfigIngressAddrXlateMode.name: svcConfigIngressAddrXlateMode
svcConfigIngressAddrXlateMode.description: This object determines the type of address translation, if any to occur for calls entering the network at this port. The tunnelling mode reverses the actions of egress tunnelling. If a called subaddress is present, it will replace the called party address, which will be discarded. If a calling subaddress is present, it will replace the calling party address, which will be discarded. The two translation modes are used for address interworking between networks using E.164 ATM Endsystem addresses and native ISDN E.164 addresses.
